        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-18T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-18T22:00:00-05:00" n="745" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/1–1949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-19T11:00:00+08:00">January 19, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 19—1:25 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. Officially notified by Chief Protocol, Foreign Office, that National
                    Government is moving Canton beginning January 21 and have been officially
                    requested to follow Government Canton. Further details with our recommendations
                    will follow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
